  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ Gas 6</p><p>Add the <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Add the<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), a pinch of<strong> salt</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a splash of <strong>water</strong></p><p>Tip: The water helps to cook the squash quicker!</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1618935204967-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1618935204967-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1618935204967-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1618935204967-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1618935204967-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop the<strong> brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice the<strong> portobello mushrooms</strong></p><p>Drain the <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper </strong>and tear it into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with <strong>kitchen paper</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1618935232464-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1618935232464-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1618935232464-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1618935232464-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1618935232464-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened, then transfer the<strong> </strong>softened<strong> </strong>onion to a plate and reserve the pan</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced mushroom</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the reserved pan and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1618935243573-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1618935243573-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1618935243573-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1618935243573-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1618935243573-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the <strong>softened</strong> <strong>onion</strong> to the pan with the <strong>spinach</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until wilted – these are your <strong>spinach &</strong> <strong>garlic mushrooms</strong></p><p>Once the squash is tender, add it to a <strong>blender </strong>(or pan if using a stick blender) with the<strong> veg stock mix</strong>, 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Blitz until smooth – this is your<strong> squash sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1618935256277-x200.jpg",
